properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in blowing snow is expected or occurring. Total snowfall: 10 to 15 cm. Maximum gusts: near 80 km/h. Locations: southwestern Newfoundland. Remarks: Strong southeasterly winds have developed in the Wreckhouse area with gusts near 80 km/h. Winds will shift to northeasterly this evening with widespread gusts near 80 km/h, before beginning to diminish overnight. Snow will combine with the wind this evening to produce poor visibility in blowing snow. The snow is expected to end around midnight. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Snow Squall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snow squalls today. A strong snow squall off of Southern Lake Huron extends from near Grand Bend across London to the Thamesford and Ingersoll areas. Snowfall amounts of 10 to 15 cm in a few hours are possible with this snow squall. In addition, sudden near zero visibility from blowing snow and bursts of heavy snow are expected as the snow squall moves in. The snow squall will move south of the area this afternoon. However new snow squalls are expected to develop off of Southern Lake Huron later this afternoon when the winds shift to a more northerly direction. These will affect Eastern Lambton County and Middlesex County mainly west of the City of London. ### Snow squalls cause weather conditions to vary considerably; changes from clear skies to heavy snow within just a few kilometres are common. Visibility will be suddenly reduced to near zero at times in heavy snow and blowing snow. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
Expires: 2020-01-20T09:07:07-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-01-19T17:08:07-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.0868278754.2020
Area: Watford - Pinery Park - Eastern Lambton County, London - Parkhill - Eastern Middlesex County, Strathroy - Komoka - Western Middlesex County

properties.Title: Winter Storm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Hazardous winter conditions are expected. A Pacific frontal system will remain stationary over the central coast today. 42 cm has been reported as of 10 am at the Bella Coola airport and another 10 cm of snow mixed with ice pellets is likely before becoming mixed with freezing rain and rain later today. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Ice build-up may cause tree branches to break. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
